				<td colspan="2"><span>I feel your pain Hash, I really do. Sometimes I wonder why I keep playing, after all, what's the differance between killing level 50 mob and level 5 mob? Not much really. When you think of the level of equipment, the time spent, the risk/reward factor it all comes out about the same.
<br />

<br />
But in the end I keep playing, becaue I've made so many friends in EQ. I find myself missing them if I don't play for a week, and wondering what they've been doing and how things are going for them. So, dispite the fact that the last thing I'm concerned with is actually <i>playing</i> EQ, I end up playing it anyway.
<br />

<br />
I suppose there will come a day when I actually walk away from EQ for good. But after four years I can't imagen when that might be.
<br />
</span></td>
