				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Are you Guys bored of EQ?<a name="33547"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 8 04 9:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>*Cough* He never said a word about tradeskill. *End Cough*
<br />

<br />
As for being bored.  I'm in the high end game and every night we raid Uqua(6 days) or Time(1 day).  And that is boring.  I have 400some aa's so exping for the actual exp is lacking as well...so why do I keep playing?
<br />

<br />
I play cause its fun.  I love getting an exp group with friends and completely obliterating a ldon or PoE.  I love going down to Trak's lair solo and accidently agroing him but still managing to get him to 80% before he banished me, then summoned me and killed me.  I love trying things everyone says are too hard and actually doing them.  And most of all, I love being a bard: Dancing among mobs to target them all with F8, pulling that illusive named from the midst of a bagillion mobs, being the person in the group who everyone looks at and says &quot;Daaaamn, I wouldn't want to have to do what he's doing.  But he sure does it well.&quot;
<br />

<br />
Why do I do this? Not because It will give me a 6 figure income in a few years.  Not because it will impart upon me infinite knowledge about the world.  I do it cause when I'm lost as h*ll in the Mushroom maze of Seb I'm grinning like theres no tomorrow and on the edge of my seat.  I do it cause, after spending days attempting The Rathe we go in one day and our guild leader gives us a speech that would have made <i>Braveheart</i> proud.  And we won.
<br />

<br />
Asking questions like this is like asking, why do we do anything? Why go to a movie? It doesn't help us in any way.  Why make friends?  Because its fun.  If it has ceased to be, then cease to do it.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
