				<td colspan="2"><span> My average stint in EQ lasts about 3 months. I play for awhile then lay off from anywhere between a month and a year.  I am in my 3rd month this time around and getting bored so I imagine I will be doing something else soon for a while.
<br />
 That beng said, I almost never return to a game after i quit the first time. I have returned to EQ maybe 6-7 times now.
<br />
I returned to Age of Kings once and Motor City Online once.
<br />
Other than that, most games have at most about a month before I lose intrest.
<br />
 I have learned to not let EQ interfere with real life, even though at times, I did let the silly game take precedence over some other things. I like having a game that fully immerses you so that you care about your character development enough to plan ahead for weeks on what you are heading for.
<br />
No other game I have played( iI have played most of the MMORPG's on the market) has kept my intrest.</span></td>
