				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Are you Guys bored of EQ?<a name="33619"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 8 04 1:29 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>EQ game revolves about just a few concepts:
<br />

<br />
1- <b>Levels</b>. You get more powerfull as you level up.
<br />
2- <b>Gear</b>. You get access to better gear as you or your guild gets more powerful.
<br />
3- <b>Group experiences</b>.
<br />
4- <b>Solo experiences</b>.
<br />
5- <b>Quest</b> (including epic).
<br />
6- <b>Tradeskills</b>.
<br />

<br />
Provided the game is old enough so that the element of surprise is long gone, you have to enjoy doing some of the cathegories stated above for the game to be entertaining.
<br />

<br />
1- <b>Levels</b>. Some people enjoy leveling up and they will grind experience to get themselves to 65 ASAP, and when that is accomplished they might start a different character to do it over. However, leveling in the same zones over and over might be a bore, trying different zones with not so good experience might help in your boredom, as well as trying different kill-tactics.
<br />

<br />
2- <b>Gear</b>. Some people farm plat in hopes of upgrading their characters thru bazaar. Others farm LDoN points to achive the same goal. Those who have the time might choose to raid with a guild to get their gear instead. If LDoN  and/or raiding bores you, you might try HARD LDoN, it is a blast, if not because of the drop (not lucky with rolls or named mobs spawns) the fact that you have to be really focused to win because the mobs have such high DPS that wipes are an ever threat is at least challenging.
<br />

<br />
3- <b>Group exp</b>. As bard, the main role is to make the group more efficient while sometimes pulling and/or sometimes doing Crowd Control. However, if the group is too powerfull relative to the mobs being killed that there isn't any close calls, and the mobs' loot is meaningless, it can become a bore. Maybe trying different zones or revamped old zones (PoFear, PoHate, PoGrowth) can help that. Maybe going to zones where experience is not so great, but mobs drop items worth getting, or just going to zones where the only thing going for them is that they are a blast, because of adds and unpredictabily of mob behaviors (mob mix) will help.
<br />

<br />
4- <b>Solo</b>. Some people like to solo AND will only solo. Again, trying different zones, mobs, feats (killing Mean_Named_Mob_01 just to see if you can solo it since being bard) might help.
<br />

<br />
5- <b>Quests</b>. Some people like questing, either because of the items or just because of talking to an NPC and trying to complete a quest no one knows about just because that's what you like of the game regardless of drop (since most quest items do suck). Others like questing keys for access to more zones and loots.
<br />

<br />
6- <b>Tradeskills</b>. Some people like tradeskilling, and the thought of being able to craft something compensates them for the ton of clicking involved in tradeskilling. Others see tradeskilling as a way to get decent items for themselves and others. At 250 level it might even have some nice return on the time and investment dedicated to tradeskilling if you like bazaar.
<br />

<br />
If none of this appeal to you, it can be due to 2 factors.
<br />

<br />
1- The class you are playing does not fit your personality and your playing style. Maybe trying a different class will work for you.
<br />

<br />
2- EQ is not entertaining you as it should or once was. The element of surprise is gone and nothing else appeals to you, thus finding a new game that offers that element of surprise you are looking for would be the thing to do.
<br />

<br />
In all, all computer games are just a bunch on 1s and 0s mixed in a different order. You just have to find the mix that appeals to you.
<br />

<br />
Nilufer,
<br />
65 Enchanter
<br />
65 Necro
<br />
65 Bard
<br />
54 Mage
<br />
36 SK
<br />
12 Beast Lord
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
