				<td colspan="2"><span>I had been losing interest for a long time, and realized a few weeks ago how very much I was bored with the game when my single group (now two groups) of friends that I had been adventuring with since we started back around Velious was doing a miniraid of Hate and I found it so engrossing that I put Flue on autofollow, started WoMarr, and just walked away, went downstairs, made a breakfast burrito from scratch, and ate most of it before returning to play.
<br />

<br />
BORING.
<br />

<br />
The only thing that has piqued my interest in the past several months is the active pickup flagging groups that will try some fairly aggressive raids with all pickup members (a pickup RZtW raid is interesting, I can tell you, if doomed to failure most of the time).  But that wastes entirely too much time.
<br />

<br />
Haven't played for about 3 weeks now and don't miss it at all, but I'm not deleting the accounts yet; I may rekindle some interest eventually.
<br />
</span></td>
